<% provide(:title, 'Info') %>

	<br>

	<div class="span4" style="background: rgba(172,228,252,.4);
                                              color:black; margin: 10px 0 0 0px; box-shadow: 10px 10px 5px #434343">

		<% if !signed_in? %>

			<p style="margin:10px 10px 10px 10px" align="justify">

					   Runnery is a restaurant delivery platform. 
	   				   Restaurants submit deliveries to a pool of local,
	   				   freelance drivers. Drivers choose the deliveries they want to run.
			</p>

	</div>

		<% elsif driver? %>

			<p align="justify">

				The driver works for their self, and uses Runnery as a way to get food-delivery jobs. Though the restaurant may give drivers money, drivers are paid by the customer.

			</p>

			<p align="justify">

				Each delivery has a surcharge. Surcharge reflects order size/cost, delivery distance, cost of gas, etc.

			</p>

			<p align="justify">

				Drivers are expected to pay for customers' cash orders up-front, minus surcharge, and be reembersed/tipped on delivery.

			</p>

			<p align="justify">

				For debited orders, surcharge is paid by the restaurant on pickup. Tip is either paid by the restuarant on pickup, or by the customer on delivery.
			</p>
			
			<p align="justify">

				For credited tips, a receipt must be redeemed by the restaurant and tips paid after. Returning to the restaurant is not required for receipts with no tip. Surcharge is always paid on pickup.

			</p>

			<br>

			<h4 align="justify">

				Be safe and use sound judgement when driving.

			</h4>
			
			<h4 align="justify">

				Know your local mobile-user driving laws and your insurance coverage for added vehical use. 

			</h4>

			<br>

			<h3 align="justify">

				Thank you! 

			</h3>

			<% else %>

			<p align="justify">

	        	 Restaurants use Runnery to inform local drivers of their deliveries. The restaurant does not employ drivers, though the restaurant may give a driver money. Drivers are paid by the customer. 

	        </p>

			<p align="justify">

				Restaurants can submit 100 orders before having to subscribe to Runnery. Runnery cost $250 for every 1000 deliveries ($0.25/del). A restaurant's delivery cost can be balanced by the surcharge charged to the customer and surcharge paid to the driver. Subscription is paid via Paypal.

			</p>

	        <p align="justify">

				Each delivery has a surcharge. Surcharge reflects order size/cost, delivery distance, cost of gas, etc.

			</p>

			<p align="justify">

				Drivers are expected to pay for cash orders up-front, minus surcharge, and be reembersed/tipped on delivery.

			</p>

			<p align="justify">

				For debited orders, surcharge is paid by the restaurant on pickup. Tip is either paid by the restuarant on pickup, or by the customer on delivery.
			</p>
			
			<p align="justify">

				For credited tips, a receipt must be redeemed by the restaurant and tips paid after. Returning to the restaurant is not required for receipts with no tip. Surcharge is always paid on pickup.

			</p>

			<p align="justify">

				The restaurant is responsible for their orders. please use good judgement when handing delivery orders over to unfamiliar drivers.

			</p> 

			<h3 align="justify">

				Thank you! 

			</h3>

	<% end %>
